<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2015/04/14/springone2gx-2014-replay-gradle-for-android">SpringOne2GX 2014 Replay: Gradle for Android</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon news-and-events"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/news">News and Events</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/c910c2f6520a5977a836d74e86e07cb4?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Pieter Humphrey</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2015-04-14 00:11:00.0">April 14, 2015</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2078" href="/blog/2015/04/14/springone2gx-2014-replay-gradle-for-android#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Recorded at SpringOne2GX 2014. </p>
<p>Speaker: Kenneth Kousen </p>
<p>G&amp;G Special Topics </p>
<p>Slides: <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/android-development-with-gradle">http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/android-development-with-gradle </a></p>
<p>At long last, Android applications are moving away from Ant or IDE builds. The new build mechanism is based on Gradle, the popular build tool from the Groovy ecosystem. This talk will introduce Gradle to Android developers and show how easy it is to integrate into Android projects.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p> <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JE_DQcCNX7w" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> </p>
</div>
</section>
